Thank you for choosing to be part of the Trimovo community. Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how Trimovo collects, uses, discloses, and safeguards your information when you interact with our token, services, website, and any other platforms related to Trimovo.
By accessing or using Trimovo, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.
________________________________________
1. Information We Collect
We collect limited personal information and only what is necessary to provide and improve our services.
1.1 Information Automatically Collected
•	Wallet Information: When you interact with Trimovo, we may collect your public wallet address.
•	Usage Data: Includes logs such as IP address, browser type, device information, access times, and pages viewed.
•	Blockchain Data: Transactions made through blockchain networks are publicly available and immutable.
1.2 Information You Provide to Us
•	If you contact us via forms, email, or social media, we may collect your name, email address, and any message contents.
•	If participating in events, rewards, or KYC-required programs (e.g., airdrops or token sales), additional personal data may be requested under compliance obligations.
________________________________________
2. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect to:
•	Operate and improve Trimovo products and services.
•	Respond to inquiries and provide support.
•	Analyze trends and performance.
•	Comply with legal and regulatory obligations.
•	Prevent fraud and maintain security.
________________________________________
3. Sharing Your Information
We do not sell or rent your personal information. We may share your data with:
•	Service Providers: Third parties that assist in hosting, analytics, security, or communications.
•	Legal Authorities: When required by law, regulation, or legal process.
•	Business Transfers: In the event of a merger, acquisition, or asset sale.
________________________________________
4. Data Retention
We retain your information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy or as required by law.
________________________________________
5. Security
We implement reasonable administrative and technical measures to protect your data. However, no method of transmission over the internet or blockchain is 100% secure.
________________________________________
6. Your Rights and Choices
Depending on your location, you may have rights to:
•	Access the information we hold about you.
•	Request corrections or deletions.
•	Withdraw consent (where applicable).
•	Lodge complaints with a data protection authority.
To exercise these rights, contact us at: trimovofun@gmail.com
________________________________________
7. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
Our website may use cookies and similar technologies to improve your experience. You can manage your cookie preferences through your browser settings.
________________________________________
8. Children’s Privacy
Trimovo is not intended for children under the age of 13 (or equivalent minimum age in your jurisdiction). We do not knowingly collect data from children.
________________________________________
9. Third-Party Links
Our services may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for their privacy practices or content.
________________________________________
10. Updates to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The revised version will be posted on our website with the “Effective Date” updated. Your continued use of Trimovo constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
________________________________________
11. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
